    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Painters who produce many works in quick succession for profit or otherwise to meet market demand, particularly as applied to Dutch painters in 17th-18th centuries. The term may carry overtones of works having mediocre quality or being of a duplicative nature.</Note_Text>
